### 3.3 ⭐ 城市数据工具层（v2架构核心）

**【Claude Code Prompt 3 — City Tools】**

```
Read CLAUDE.md. Create lib/city-tools.ts — the tool layer that Claude calls during chat.

Define both the tool SCHEMAS (Anthropic tool format) and the EXECUTORS:

Tool 1 — search_events
  description: "Search currently active and predicted events in the city. Use this whenever the user asks what's happening, about safety, traffic, or any specific area."
  input_schema: { category?: EventCategory, neighborhood?: string, near?: {lat, lng}, radius_miles?: number, include_predicted?: boolean, max_results?: number }
  executor: filters SEATTLE_EVENTS (+ live events passed in), computes distances with haversine, returns compact JSON (id, title, category, severity, distance, heatScore, status, predictedPeakAt) — NOT full objects, keep token use low.

Tool 2 — query_poi
  description: "Look up places (restaurants, venues, parks, landmarks) from the POI database. Use for any recommendation or 'where is' question."
  input_schema: { query?: string, category?: string, neighborhood?: string, near?: {lat,lng}, exclude_near_events?: boolean, max_results?: number }
  executor: searches SEATTLE_POIS by fuzzy name/category match. If exclude_near_events is true, filter out POIs within 0.3mi of any active high-severity event — this powers the killer demo query "find me dinner away from the chaos".

Tool 3 — get_predictions
  description: "Get AI predictions about what will happen in the next few hours: traffic surges, crowd buildups, event peaks."
  input_schema: { hours_ahead?: number, category?: EventCategory }
  executor: returns the predicted-status events plus output from lib/prediction-engine.ts.

Tool 4 — get_area_status
  description: "Get the overall pulse of a neighborhood: heat score, trend, active event count."
  input_schema: { neighborhood: string }
  executor: looks up CITY_STATS + counts events in that neighborhood.

Export: CITY_TOOLS (array of tool schemas) and executeTool(name, input): Promise<string> that routes to the right executor and returns JSON string. Also export TOOL_LABELS: a map from tool name to human-readable label like "Searching active events..." for the UI indicator.
```

### 3.4 ⭐ 对话API：Tool Use + 流式（整个项目最重要的文件）

**【Claude Code Prompt 4 — Chat API】**

```
Read CLAUDE.md. Create app/api/chat/route.ts — the conversational city query API.

Architecture: Claude with TOOL USE in an agentic loop, streamed to the client via Server-Sent Events.

1. POST handler accepts: { messages: ChatMessage[], location?: {lat, lng} }

2. System prompt (keep it SHORT now that tools carry the data):
   - "You are PulseCity's AI city guide for Seattle. You have live access to the city's event feed, POI database, and prediction engine through your tools. ALWAYS use tools to answer — never guess about current events."
   - Current timestamp + day of week
   - Personality rules: have opinions, lead with the most important thing, give ONE specific recommendation not a list, use natural distance language ("3 blocks north"), under 100 words, end with one "→" action suggestion when relevant
   - When mentioning a specific POI from query_poi results, wrap it as <poi id="POI_ID">Name</poi>
   - For predictions, phrase as "I'm tracking..." or "Based on the patterns I'm seeing..."

3. Agentic loop with the Anthropic SDK:
   - model: 'claude-sonnet-4-6', max_tokens: 600, tools: CITY_TOOLS
   - While the response has stop_reason 'tool_use': execute each tool call via executeTool(), append tool_result blocks, call the API again. Cap at 5 iterations.
   - For each tool call, immediately emit an SSE event: { type: 'tool_call', tool, label } and on completion { type: 'tool_done', tool }
   - For the final text response, use streaming and emit { type: 'text_delta', text } chunks as they arrive
   - End with { type: 'done', referencedPois: POI[] } — parse <poi> tags from the full text and resolve them against SEATTLE_POIS

4. SSE format: standard 'data: {json}\n\n' lines, Content-Type text/event-stream, no caching.

5. Error handling: any API failure emits { type: 'error', message } — never crash the stream.

Also create lib/chat-client.ts: a client-side function streamCityChat(messages, location, callbacks) using fetch + ReadableStream parsing, with callbacks: onToolCall, onToolDone, onTextDelta, onDone, onError.
```

### 3.5 ⭐ Reddit + Haiku事件分类

**【Claude Code Prompt 5 — Reddit与AI分类】**

```
Read CLAUDE.md. Create lib/reddit-client.ts, lib/classify-events.ts, and app/api/reddit/route.ts.

reddit-client.ts:
- OAuth2 client_credentials flow, token cached in memory with expiry
- fetchLocalPosts(subreddits: string[], limit): hot posts from r/Seattle, r/SeattleWA
- Exponential backoff on rate limits. All errors return [] silently (demo must never break).

classify-events.ts — AI classification replacing keyword matching:
- classifyPosts(posts: RedditPost[]): Promise<CityEvent[]>
- ONE batched call to claude-haiku-4-5 (not one call per post): send up to 15 post titles+snippets, ask for a JSON array back.
- For each post the model returns: { is_local_event: boolean, category, severity, title (cleaned up), summary (one sentence), location_mention: string | null, confidence: number }
- Prompt the model to respond ONLY with the JSON array, no prose. Strip ```json fences before parsing. Discard items with is_local_event false or confidence < 0.6.
- Map location_mention to coordinates using a lookup table of ~25 common Seattle place names → real lat/lng. If no match, drop the event (better to miss than to misplace a pin).
- Build CityEvent objects with source platform 'Reddit', credibility 0.65, heatScore derived from post score (upvotes), expiresAt = createdAt + 12h.

app/api/reddit/route.ts:
- GET: fetch posts → classify → merge with SEATTLE_EVENTS (mock first)
- 3s timeout on the whole Reddit pipeline; on timeout return mock only
- Cache 5 minutes (Next.js revalidate)
```

